      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NIFTY SCHOOBEE (1) was a beaten favourite last week but was good in leading from a wider barrier for second at Leeton the run prior. Has the speed to take advantage of the ace draw and has recorded a win and a placing in two attempts at this circuit and distance. THE DEMOCRAT (4) wasn't too far away in a higher-graded race last time. Better placed here having come from the back line for a 1.3m second in a similar class to this two back at Maryborough. MELATI BOY (8) raced parked and stuck on for second at Wagga two back then was solid enough from this row last start. Has trialled well since so could be ready to peak now. A good draw brings BETTERTHANTHEBOYZ (2) right into contention.",
